research\e6-reputational-competition-design.md-14-- Each executor has fixed **ability** a_i ~ U(0.3, 0.9) and chooses **effort** e_i ∈ [0, 1] each cycle. A delivered milestone's quality is q = 0.25 + 0.45·a_i + 0.30·e_i (bounded to [0,1]). Effort is costly (convex), so absent returns, rational effort decays toward zero.
research\e6-reputational-competition-design.md-15-- **Reputation** R_i = running mean of an executor's verified milestone quality — recorded only where the regime measures delivery.
research\e6-reputational-competition-design.md:16:- **Behavioral rule** (bounded rationality, seeded): each cycle, with probability 0.3, an executor compares itself to a visible high-assignment performer and moves its effort 20% toward that performer's effort (imitation of success — possible only where reputation and assignments are visible); where nothing is visible, effort decays 10% toward zero (cost minimization); small seeded exploration noise (±0.05) throughout.
