RELEASING.md:1:# Release flow (papers → GitHub release → Zenodo)
RELEASING.md-2-
RELEASING.md:3:Codified 2026-07-07 after the v1.9 cycle, to keep DOIs from going stale inside deposited PDFs.
RELEASING.md-4-
RELEASING.md-5-## The DOI rule
RELEASING.md-6-
RELEASING.md:7:- **Paper headers cite the concept DOI** (`10.5281/zenodo.21193846`): it never changes and always resolves
RELEASING.md:8:  to the latest deposited version, so a PDF header can never be stale again. (Single record — the whole
RELEASING.md:9:  deposit, corpus + manuscript + code, is CC BY 4.0 / MIT.)
RELEASING.md:10:- **Version DOIs** live where they are knowable: CITATION.cff, the GitHub release notes, and the Zenodo record.
RELEASING.md:11:- If an exact version DOI inside the PDF is ever wanted, use **pre-reservation**: create the Zenodo new-version *draft first*, read its pre-reserved DOI (`metadata.prereserve_doi`), render the PDFs citing it, upload, then publish. Order: draft → render → upload → publish.
RELEASING.md-12-
RELEASING.md-13-## The version-string rule (anti-recurrence guard for C026)
RELEASING.md-14-
RELEASING.md:15:Whenever the **draft** version changes (the `drafts/paper.md` header), **immediately** sync the version *strings* in `CITATION.cff` (`version`), `.zenodo.json` (`version` + title suffix), and `README.md` — even between deposits, with Zenodo paused. The metadata version string must never lag the draft. (DOIs are separate: headers cite the concept DOI; version DOIs are only swept on an actual deposit.) This drift recurred at v1.8→v1.12 (2026-07-10) exactly because the draft moved without a deposit.
RELEASING.md-16-
RELEASING.md:17:## License note (author decision, 2026-07-10)
RELEASING.md-18-
RELEASING.md:19:The whole deposit is **CC BY 4.0** for all text and research content (corpus + manuscript) and **MIT** for
RELEASING.md:20:code — a single record, one concept-DOI lineage (`10.5281/zenodo.21193846`; latest version
RELEASING.md:21:`10.5281/zenodo.21252911` = v1.12). CC BY attribution applies to text/research content; MIT requires notice retention for code. (An earlier plan to protect the
RELEASING.md-22-manuscript under CC BY-NC-ND with a separate record was dropped: the code/corpus are already public, so a
RELEASING.md:23:protected manuscript would not have protected the implementation, and the author chose full openness.)
RELEASING.md-24-
RELEASING.md-25-## The cycle
RELEASING.md-26-
RELEASING.md:27:1. Edit `drafts/paper.md` and mirror in `drafts/paper.es.md` (English is authoritative).
RELEASING.md-28-2. `npm run check-anchors` clean.
RELEASING.md-29-3. Render four outputs with `scripts/md-to-pdf.mjs` (`--lang en|es`, `--toc`, `--html` for the screen-reader edition); rasterize a few pages (PyMuPDF) and inspect them before shipping.
RELEASING.md:30:4. Commit, tag `vX.Y`, `gh release create` with the four renders attached.
RELEASING.md:31:5. Zenodo new version on the deposition id in `_backups/zenodo-depid.txt` (a non-secret id). **Supply the API token through an environment variable at deposit time — `ZENODO_TOKEN`, exported into the shell session only (read it from your OS credential store / password manager) — never a token file left in the repo tree.** New-version draft → replace files (corpus + manuscript renders + code) → bump `version`/`publication_date` → publish → update the depid file.
RELEASING.md-32-6. Sweep the *version* DOI across CITATION.cff/README notes (headers stay on the concept DOI).
RELEASING.md-33-
RELEASING.md-34-## Credential handling (security)
RELEASING.md-35-
RELEASING.md:36:The Zenodo API token is a release-account credential: treat it as a secret.
RELEASING.md:37:- **Never persist it to a file in the working tree** (an earlier version of this flow named `_backups/zenodo-token.txt`; that pattern is retired). Pass it via `ZENODO_TOKEN` in the shell session, or a protected CI secret if the deposit is ever automated.
RELEASING.md:38:- `_backups/` is git-ignored so a stray credential there can never be committed, but git-ignore is not protection: **if a `zenodo-token.txt` was ever created, delete it and rotate the token** in the Zenodo account settings.
RELEASING.md:39:- Scope the token to the minimum needed (`deposit:write`, `deposit:actions`).
